snippet.textDisplay:
I have heard Abida Begum live in Mumbai. It was organised by Times music and the venue was bandra fort.
I did not have any tickets on me for the show but I still travelled for a hour and half because I was very determined to attend her live concert in Mumbai because I knew that was once in a life appournity. I went around asking people if they had a ticket to spare and a god sent person approached me and offered me 2 spare tickets. In turn I shared 1spare ticket with a random person whom I thought was someone like me, complete stranger, but coincidentally he turned out to be one of my clients brother! The world is very small...
I have several similar experiences where I did not have any tickets for the show but yet I somehow managed to attend them. Doesn't matter if you have to beg/request for tickets or entry.
I have once watched Zakir Hussain sitting on the floor in the asile! The kind authorities allowed several of us without tickets but asked them to sit on the floor but luckily we eventually got transferred on the seats.
If the music is good then and you have the craze to listen that then you must not bother about the tickets or not being able to afford. Just go to the venue and you will find your way
